The paper deals with the construction of binary linear codes for storage systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The codes are constructed using cyclic codes, which are a type of algebraic code and fall under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the optimization of code dimension, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper extends the construction to build codes with multiple repair sets, which involves network algorithms (cs.NA) and possibly social networks (cs.SI).
